Antenna (
Fig. 41b
). Radicles and scape yellow; A3–A12 brown; A1 length: 14; A2 shorter than A3.

Mesosoma
. Color brown (
Fig. 84
). In dorsal view mesoscutum and mesoscutellum imbricate; in lateral view speculum with furrow; femoral depression smooth with fan-like striation starting by post-ventral angle; posterior mesepimeral area not well delimitate anteriorly; dorsal and ventral metapleural area with crenulate depression with rugae (
Fig. 84
); metapleural carina with one posterior pointed projection (
Fig. 85
). Metascutellum visible in dorsal view, wide with margins parallel to mesoscutellum ones, small metanotal spine (
Fig. 85
).

On T1 pair of longitudinal submedial carinae, aligned with the metapleural carinae, separating lateral coriaceous scupture from internal smooth area; In the middle of T1 a sculpure striate to coriaceous starting from anterior margin and gradually dissolving towards posterior margin (
Figs 84, 85
). T2 not foveolate in anterior margin, rugose-coriaceous, short longitudinal wrinkles not surpassing 1/5 of the metasoma, rugose-coriaceous in the other tergites (
Fig. 81
).

Mesosoma
. In dorsal view, mesonotum anteriorly dark yellow to brown; mesoscutellum brown with posterior margin yellow; propodeum dark yellow; metascutellum and metanotal spine brown (
Fig. 80
). In lateral view, from dorsal margin yellowish to brown (
Fig. 83
).

In dorsal view mesonotum and mesoscutellum imbricate (
Fig. 80
); in lateral view speculum with furrow; femoral depression smooth with fan-like striation starting by post-ventral angle; posterior mesepimeral area not well delimitate anteriorly; dorsal and ventral metapleural area with crenulate depression with rugae (
Fig. 83
); metapleural carina with one posterior pointed projection (
Fig. 80
). Metascutellum visible in dorsal view, wide with margins parallel to mesoscutellum ones, small metanotal spine (
Fig. 80
).

Metasoma
. In dorsal view metasoma anteriorly yellowish as in propodeum, color changes gradually in dark brown in last tergite; T1, T2, T3 color light brown on side; laterotergites yellowish (
Fig. 81
). On T1 pair of longitudinal submedial carinae, aligned with the metapleural carinae, separating lateral coriaceous scupture from internal smooth area; in the middle of T1 a sculpure striate to coriaceous starting from anterior margin and gradually dissolving towards posterior margin (
Fig. 80, 81
). T2 not foveolate in anterior margin, rugosecoriaceous, short longitudinal wrinkles not surpassing 1/5 of the metasoma, rugose-coriaceous in the other tergites (
Fig. 81
).
